[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering OGNL’s setup**\n\nI’m looking into OGNL and thinking about whether we need to use `jar tf`, which might not be necessary. There’s also the dependency convergence aspect to review. The documentation for general use without Docker should help with that. So, OGNL includes a security manager controlled by a property, but meaningful coverage doesn’t require the environment to be set up. I’ll note that for tests, we can manage the security manager, especially with changes in JDK25. I’m curious if this is the correct setup guidance for users.\n\n**Exploring dependency info**\n\nI think I might need to run some dependency info from the POM file—it seems like that could be enough. When I consider investigating the resolved artifacts and dependencies, I could use something like curl on the POM and inspect the classes. There’s also the possibility of checking `module-info`. Maybe I should use `jar tf` in a temporary location to get a good overview. It feels like there's a lot I could explore here!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0005d0ed81ecbe8c016a3f21f4dc1c8197a087e4a735e451ff\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPyH9CvuQX_P0vbkPFgLnrIYnc0VtC5bHSLoKemSu9VfgL0VV5CLcwABP6d1cxF8l2TXMKAPodpr93XigSpWZOuB7FpaymhGxe0TieFIFtrGfBcqpqCPCae6Ei1_yXDouRvo5dIbHsaGPeAHF5-HUpmUzvVCQODL9KU2KJBr3y6sodX02YR3HecaIRdtUSqiVrv-L5TwIhEEySmfYnO9MtPTlvyQikVdr-PcwUNCJIru5KUkYHZHdATXWqKo0gID6fCACUc1S-dNt_JB301lGYA9XQWsw4Fe8jEwNyhS4H_gHwt1XwKD98db-mrFL_5UjT1-Fc3WHsdqtRWUTn0rjTtCNSTM9gFIa3qlXql4-ExzSaISDsApX1NjXR-kMfCRlNUQ3gCJSJuoLLIXdg3nWLFRKOzcXX8FYTeS0ZiMb9Fs_XUWZ47fDeNpg6a4hewklyDepuvci_BWGmhZzR9sg0ipfkOBmJMXZRq0RUa7gmHGdAPb1FlStHlG5FuP9uBHGWtgdBv5Px9W3mXVNWTEETX6a29k1XXArEwzAC_7T3HfQUo35vGR5ji5vxe3LO0USttpwkOSZvSdtzZztfOsRCOrFaF0gKpMPBaUHvhPBDiR_8zMTaDEZrkGYRlGCx2qxYSYZlFlZ1ti6jz-Y-emb4GSyTKZeguzIkZM2r-De1ZG2RCXJ5dGJWTGfZ7n5hwjZJTDE_6YhgS