[thinking] **Evaluating JDK security settings**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m noticing that in JDK25, the SecurityManager API might be marked for removal, which could have implications for dynamic installs being disabled unless a specific property, `-Djava.security.manager=allow`, is set. With JDK18 and above, enabling the SecurityManager seems to be possible by adjusting the right property. It’s interesting to consider how these changes will affect security practices moving forward!
[thinking] 
