te/member-access behavior, configure the test JVM with `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` and likely `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`, matching upstream OGNL's JDK 17+ test profile. Avoid relying on unguarded `System.setSecurityManager` on JDK 25; if sandbox behavior is covered, set/restore `ognl.security.manager` inside the test and tolerate dynamic SecurityManager installation being unsupported.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Basic parse/get/set OGNL usage may pass without module opens, but coverage of the reflection and accessibility paths that matter for reachability metadata can fail or be skipped without them.\",\n    \"SecurityManager-related OGNL paths are fragile on modern JDKs and should be guarded rather than treated as mandatory JVM setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0005d0ed81ecbe8c016a3f2207131c8197916f7828cea742ee\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2046, "output": 824, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24886, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782522366378, "responseId": "resp_0005d0ed81ecbe8c016a3f21fed3308197ba1c387c57bfd29e"}, "toolResults": []}
